{
  "texts": [
    "Joint-design ISACDifferent from the above-mentioned ISAC systems, the joint-design ones directly optimize the dualfunctional signal according to the communication and sensing requirements without leveraging the communication or sensing signal.",
    "Therefore, the joint-design scheme breaks through the limitations of communication or radar standards, enjoying more design flexibility.",
    "A general optimization problem for the joint-design ISAC system can be formulated as [78] maxX U (Y, X) (12a) s.t.",
    "C i (Y, X) c i, i = 1,..., M,(12b)S j (Y, X) s j, j = 1,..., J,where represents neither, or =, U is the utility function, and X and Y stand for the sets of optimization variables and system parameters, respectively.",
    "C i stands for the ith communication utility function with the threshold c i."
  ]
}